    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1899-12-27T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1899-12-27T00:00:00-05:00" n="650"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d650">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Cridler</persName> to Mr. <persName
                            type="to">Hollis</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1899-12-27">
                            <hi rend="italic">December 27, 1899</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 50.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I inclose copies of two letters<note n="2"
                        xml:id="d650fn2">(Inclosures:) From Hopkins &amp; Hopkins, December 12,
                        1899, and December 15, 1899, printed ante.</note> from Messrs. Hopkins &amp;
                    Hopkins, complaining of the action of the British Government in seizing, off
                    Delagoa Bay, the steamships <hi rend="italic">Mashona</hi> and <hi rend="italic"
                        >Maria</hi>, both of which carried goods shipped by Messrs. Flint, Eddy
                    &amp; Co., of New York. You will please investigate the matter and report
                    thereon to the Department. You will also use all proper efforts to protect the
                    property of the American shippers.</p>
                <p>I am, etc.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Thos. W. Cridler</hi>,<lb/>
                        <hi rend="italic">Third Assistant Secretary.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
